The paper deals with the problem of Private Information Retrieval (PIR) with coded side information, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multiple servers and the focus on server-symmetric schemes suggest that the paper may also be relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and networking (cs.SI). Finally, the study of capacity and rate in PIR-CSI schemes involves coding theory (cs.CC).
